This folder contains three files:
- pairings.sage contains only the functions necessary to evaluate the pairings
- Weil_and_Tate_Pairings.ipynb is jupyter notebook that contains all the functions ordered in a meaningful way with also some test and the possibility to try actively the script
- Weil_and_Tate_Pairngs.html is an html version (view only) of the notebook

To open the jupyter notebook (supposing it to be installed) you need to execute:
sage -n jupyter
on the command line and navigate to the file through the UI.

